176
00:13:22,790 --> 00:13:29,992
Do people who identify as having a disability feel that this is a welcoming city?

177
00:13:30,092 --> 00:13:31,473
Or was it the location?

178
00:13:31,553 --> 00:13:33,753
Was it transport?

179
00:13:34,134 --> 00:13:41,296
So these are things that you keep in mind and you use as part of your evaluation for moving forward.

180
00:13:41,856 --> 00:13:47,557
However, as a first time, I think it was wonderful.

181
00:13:47,757 --> 00:13:48,718
It gave the,

182
00:13:49,973 --> 00:13:56,418
It gave the commission an identity, started to cement that identity for the commission.

183
00:13:58,800 --> 00:14:03,363
So from that, I will segue into the vaccine clinic.

184
00:14:04,324 --> 00:14:11,790
As you know, we were gifted a mobile vaccine clinic by the Massachusetts

185
00:14:12,731 --> 00:14:20,176
Developmental Disabilities Council, so that was their part for the disability fair.

186
00:14:22,325 --> 00:14:31,648
It was, and the vaccines were gonna be administered by Cataldo, who has a partnership with the Department of Public Health.

187
00:14:31,688 --> 00:14:33,149
So that's a complete mouthful.

188
00:14:33,749 --> 00:14:38,331
However, the state did not release the vaccines in time.

189
00:14:38,411 --> 00:14:41,512
They pushed the release date back until afterwards.

190
00:14:42,212 --> 00:14:46,094
So the vaccines were finally released on November 17th,

191
00:14:48,155 --> 00:14:52,119
We still had the rights for the gift and we had the mobile clinic here.

192
00:14:52,139 --> 00:15:04,813
23 flu vaccinations were given out and 53 COVID vaccinations were also given out at the mobile vaccine clinic.

193
00:15:05,834 --> 00:15:19,620
I just, you know, I sent an email to Fatima on behalf of the commission thanking for the gift of the mobile clinic and sharing the data provided by it's how to.

194
00:15:23,339 --> 00:15:24,860
That's where we are with that.

195
00:15:24,921 --> 00:15:35,591
Does anybody have anything else that they want to add in regards to the disability fair or the mobile vaccine clinic?

196
00:15:37,352 --> 00:15:38,253
I actually would.

197
00:15:38,473 --> 00:15:42,377
I thought about this a lot, is the weather was horrible.

198
00:15:43,818 --> 00:15:47,541
It was, I don't remember, windy, rainy, something.

199
00:15:48,001 --> 00:15:53,345
And I remember Joe being worried about his balloons, which were lovely, blowing away.

200
00:15:53,365 --> 00:16:01,750
And so weather, especially with disabled, is a huge factor.

201
00:16:02,691 --> 00:16:08,535
Also, I don't know how many people really know

202
00:16:09,607 --> 00:16:22,416
Brooks School, a lot of people, and I see a lot of events happening at more at, not the Roberts School, up from there, Andrews and the one next to it.

203
00:16:23,297 --> 00:16:37,647
