204
00:16:39,506 --> 00:16:47,989
Whereas Brooks, maybe I'm wrong, is more higher income and not as many disabled.

205
00:16:49,409 --> 00:16:50,970
I could be totally wrong.

206
00:16:52,410 --> 00:16:52,990
I could be.

207
00:16:54,691 --> 00:16:59,032
So I think where we do it is really important.

208
00:16:59,952 --> 00:17:04,554
And then the weather, I said that already.

209
00:17:05,154 --> 00:17:08,235
But I think the people and the sponsors that were there

210
00:17:08,953 --> 00:17:14,177
were excited because they saw us starting to do the flame.

211
00:17:14,997 --> 00:17:17,159
And that was what was exciting to them.

212
00:17:17,719 --> 00:17:23,243
There was a woman who was running some company and I wish I knew what it was.

213
00:17:23,923 --> 00:17:27,326
And she looked at me and she said, I'm the boss of this company.

214
00:17:28,046 --> 00:17:30,428
And I can't remember whether she was

215
00:17:31,195 --> 00:17:35,556
how she was disabled, whether she was a little person or something.

216
00:17:36,136 --> 00:17:39,117
And she was excited that we were bringing it to Medford.

217
00:17:39,737 --> 00:17:47,279
